    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and chop 2/3 of your <strong>red onion[s]</strong> into wedges</p><p>Dice the <strong>remaining red onion</strong> finely</p><p>Chop your <strong>garlic </strong>finely</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-cuban-style-beef-and-pepper-stew/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Deseed your <strong>pepper[s] </strong>(scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and chop into rough chunks</p><p>Chop your <strong>coriander </strong>finely</p><p>Drain and rinse your <strong>black beans</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-cuban-style-beef-and-pepper-stew/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine the <strong>diced onion</strong> and <strong>chopped coriander</strong> in a small bowl \u2013 this is your <strong>herby topping</strong></p><p>Dissolve your <strong>beef stock mix</strong>, <strong>tomato paste</strong> and <strong>red wine stock</strong> in 500ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[650ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[850ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>tomato</strong> <strong>stock</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-cuban-style-beef-and-pepper-stew/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based <strong>hob-safe</strong> <strong>oven-proof casserole dish </strong>with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>diced</strong> <strong>beef </strong>to the dish with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Cook for 3-4 min or until starting to brown</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-cuban-style-beef-and-pepper-stew/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Reduce the heat to medium and add the <strong>red</strong> <strong>onion wedges</strong> and <strong>chopped pepper</strong> to the dish with 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp] </span><strong>flour</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>crushed garlic</strong>, <strong>black beans</strong>, <strong>smoked paprika</strong>, <strong>bay leaf[ves]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span></strong>and <strong>ground cumin</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-cuban-style-beef-and-pepper-stew/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>tomato stock</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cover with the lid and put the dish in the oven for 1 hour or until the sauce is rich and the beef is tender \u2013 this is your<strong> one-pot Cuban-style beef & pepper stew</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-cuban-style-beef-and-pepper-stew/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the stew has been cooking for 45 min, add your <strong>white long grain rice </strong>to a pot with a lid with 225ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[300ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[450ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 12-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once done, remove from the heat and set aside (lid on) to steam until serving</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-cuban-style-beef-and-pepper-stew/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> one-pot Cuban-style beef & pepper stew</strong> over the <strong>cooked rice </strong>and discard the <strong>bay leaf[ves]</strong></p><p>Sprinkle over the <strong>herby topping</strong></p><p><strong><span class=\"text-danger\">Tip: Cooking for kids? Leave out the herby topping!</span></strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
